1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) - The paper discusses the susceptibility of deep neural networks to adversarial attacks and proposes a physical attack on DNN models. This is a common topic in computer vision research.
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper proposes a novel attack method for black-box DNN models, which falls under the domain of machine learning.
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper discusses the vulnerability of DNN models to adversarial attacks, which is a common topic in the field of artificial intelligence.
4. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper proposes a method for generating physical adversarial examples, which is a security concern for DNN models.
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the robustness of the proposed attack in the real world, which involves multimedia aspects such as image and video processing.
